news.title: Copy 2
news.content: All is well on our largest neighbor; NASA's Juno spacecraft just managed to spot the shadow of Jupiter's moon, Io, passing over its marbled clouds.

news.title: Copy 3
news.content: As NASA makes a big push to land humans on the moon's surface by 2024, the European Space Agency (ESA) wants to learn more about the lunar caves that lie beneath.

news.title: The Second Moon
news.content: NASA scientists calculated that Earth should have captured a second moon on Sunday (Sept. 29)

news.title: Annular solar eclipse 2024
news.content: On Wednesday, Oct. 2, the sun will be transformed into a dramatic ring of fire as an annular solar eclipse sweeps over Hawaii, southern Chile, and southern Argentina.
